//Configure Maven in Jenkins
//Set up Maven as a tool in Jenkins to enable builds.

Go to Manage Jenkins → Global Tool Configuration → Maven Installation

Click Add Maven

Provide a name (e.g., Maven-3.8.6)

Save the configuration


//Create or Open a Jenkins Job
//Prepare the job where Maven will be used.

Navigate to your Jenkins dashboard

Select an existing job or create a new one

//Add Maven Build Step
//Specify Maven goals for the build process.

In job configuration → Build Steps → Invoke top-level Maven targets

Select the Maven installation you created earlier

Enter goals such as clean install or clean package

Do not prefix with mvn — Jenkins automatically uses Maven


// Save and Trigger Build
// Run the job to verify Maven execution.

Click Save

Select Build Now to start the process


// Handle Build Failures
// Common Issues
// Resolve frequent problems encountered during Maven builds.

Ensure the correct Maven installation is selected in the build step

Verify that a valid POM.xml file exists in the project root

Without a POM.xml, the build will fail


//Useful Maven Commands
//Common commands to run Maven tasks.

mvn compile

mvn test

mvn package

mvn install

mvn clean

